main event: Two witnesses reported seeing a stationary bright object in the sky near DeWitt, Arkansas on April 13, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 20 minutes,The witnesses described the object as bright yellowish-white and larger than a star,The observers noted that the skies were cloudy with cirrostratus clouds,One of the witnesses had military experience as a geologist and previous cryptographic training,The object was compared to Venus in brightness and appearance.
sighted object: a bright stationary object in the sky
witness description: Two civilian witnesses traveling southbound on U.S. 165.
